dsheet-based estimator I built a few years ago. But here&#8217;s a question &#8211; do you actually *show* all of this to the client, down to the task level, so that they can see how thorough you are, or do you only show them a summary of it so as not to overwhelm them? Does it depend on the size of the client?</p><div class="commentmeta"><div class="reply"> <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2009/06/11/effective-strategy-to-estimate-time-for-your-design-projects/?replytocom=357559#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-357559", "357559", "respond", "7742")'>Reply</a></div></div></div></div></li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 clearfix "> <span class="commentnumber">43</span><div class="comment" id="comment-357568"><div class="commentrating clearfix"><div class="rateresult">0</div> <a class="ratebtn down_active" id="btn-357568-down" style="opacity:0.3;" title="Vote down! (0 votes)"></a> <a class="ratebtn up_active" id="btn-357568-up" style="opacity:0.3;" title="Vote up! (0 votes)"></a></div><div class="gravatar"> <img alt='' src="http://media.smashingmagazine.com/cdn_smash/wp-content/themes/default-autosvn-stable/images/gravatar_default.png" lowsrc='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2accd1e49fd7dcd3ed55762678bca749?s=38&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D38&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-38 photo' height='38' width='38' /></div><div class="comment-text"><div class="comment-author">Bennie Mosher</div> <span class="date">June 11th, 2009</span> <span class="time">11:49 am</span><p>One thing that I try to do is use a program like &#8220;Things&#8221; or &#8220;The Hit List&#8221; to track how long different steps take me, and than I can determine from there how long another project like that will take. That&#8217;s my opinion. Awesome write up though, very interesting.</p><div class="commentmeta"><div class="reply"> <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2009/06/11/effect